-- Greece Asks for EU Aid
-- Maria Petrakis
-- 2010-04-23T10:08:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/greece-plans-to-ask-for-eu-imf-aid-package-immediately-papandreou-says.html

          
          
             Greek Prime Minister George
Papandreou said his government needs to trigger a European
Union-led rescue plan.  
 "It is a matter of national need to ask officially" for a
rescue, Papandreou said on state television. Papandreou spoke
to Greek Finance Minister George Papaconstantinou and gave
him the mandate to proceed with procedures for activation.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Petrakis in Athens at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     George Papandreou, Greece's prime minister, speaks at a press conference following the European Union Summit in Brussels, on March 26, 2010. Photographer: Jock Fistick/Bloomberg  
                           

     
